(43, 10, 13, 44, 18, 17, 17, 'careth not for the sheep', 'Carelessness of Leaders', 'This connection highlights the theme of leaders who do not care for those they are responsible for. In both passages, the hireling and Gallio exhibit a lack of concern for the well-being of others, emphasizing their indifference.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
